body.description: Learning fun is a tap away with the laptop touch 2-in-1 laptop. Kids can learn about letters, numbers, music and more on a laptop that's made just for them. Open the laptop to see the screen in keyboard mode, then close the laptop and watch the screen magically swivel into tablet mode. The laptop features an A-Z keyboard and number buttons 1-10, while the tablet features a touch screen. Kids will have fun pretending to email Scout, or tapping away in five learning modes--abcs, numbers, games, music and messages. PLUS, the laptop can be customized to help your child spell their name. The take-along handle makes it great for learning on the go!.

Make It Their Own Parents can customize the laptop to help their child spell their name. Be Big and Little Pretend to be like mom and dad with fun computer role-play, like emailing Scout. Learn & Play Five learning modes include ABCs, Numbers, Games, Music and Messages.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Product Quality with Precise Touchscreen
reviews.reviewText: Excellent Product Quality with Precise Touchscreen This learning tablet has high quality materials and construction. The touchscreen is very responsive and activates when rotated, making it easy for young kids to use. It has a full QWERTY keyboard with numbers, perfect for ages 2 and up. There are age-appropriate learning activities including letter recognition associated with animals, basic number skills, spelling words, and more. Power saving features auto-shutoff after inactivity. Batteries are included. Shipping was fast - it arrived a couple days early! Overall, this is a thoughtfully designed, high quality learning tablet with great activities to help young kids build early literacy and math skills. The touchscreen is precise and easy to use. I would highly recommend this product to parents looking for a toddler learning tablet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great alternate screentime
reviews.reviewText: It is a brilliant blend of entertainment and education for young minds. This interactive device seamlessly combines play and learning, providing a touchscreen laptop experience designed specifically for early learners.The vibrant pink color adds a delightful touch, attracting kids' attention while the interactive features engage them in a world of educational activities. From introducing letters and numbers to fostering early computer skills, this LeapTop offers a well-rounded learning experience.The durable design ensures it can withstand the enthusiastic handling of young children, and the 2-in-1 functionality allows it to be used both as a laptop and a tablet for versatile play. The touchscreen functionality adds an extra layer of engagement, making learning feel like a fun and interactive adventure.As a parent, I appreciate the thoughtful inclusion of various learning modes that adapt to a child's developmental stage. The LeapFrog 2-in-1 LeapTop Touch has become a valuable tool in our household, providing a safe and enjoyable introduction to technology while fostering essential early learning skills. It's a five-star recommendation for parents seeking a well-designed, educational device for their little ones.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My daughter used it for about 2 years, definitely a buy!!
reviews.reviewText: First and foremost, the LeapTop Touch offers an interactive and dynamic learning experience. Combining the features of both a laptop and a tablet, it provides children with a versatile platform to explore various educational activities and games. This dual functionality encourages imaginative play and helps in developing essential skills like letters, numbers, shapes, and more in an entertaining manner.The touch-sensitive screen is responsive and intuitive, making it easy for kids to navigate through different activities. It introduces them to the concept of technology in a safe and controlled environment, preparing them for the digital world while ensuring age-appropriate content.The green color and the laptop-like design are appealing to kids, making learning sessions more engaging and enjoyable. The device is also durable and built to withstand the playful handling of young children.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Toddler can do "homework"
reviews.reviewText: Great interactive games. Seems very durable even after a few throws from the little one. Love the two styles (laptop and tablet). The games are cute for little ones to learn the alphabet and some animals, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice interactive toy but the screen is not very clear. Hard to see unless it's held at the perfect angle and even then it's not a clear resolution. The screen also swings a little too much unless it's folded pretty far back. It's meant to be used from a low angle only (like the floor) and not on a table.
